## Retro Summary: openai-rust — **7.2/10**

### Key Metrics (4 pipeline runs, 5 plan tracks)
- **23 iterations**, 16 productive (70%), 7 wasted (30%)
- **65 commits**, 100% conventional format
- **141 tests**, all passing, zero clippy warnings
- **v0.4.0** published on crates.io
- **~139 min** total wall time

### Top 3 Failure Patterns
1. **Deploy AskUserQuestion blocking** — 7/7 wasted iters. 3rd project with this exact defect. Deploy asks user questions in pipeline mode where nobody can answer.
2. **Redo loops** — 3 cycles, but all productive (real fixes). Redo limit (2) worked correctly.
3. No other patterns — runs 3-4 were **zero-waste**.

### Top 3 Recommendations
1. **[CRITICAL]** Fix deploy skill — suppress `AskUserQuestion` in pipeline mode. Auto-resolve naming/versioning from `Cargo.toml` and git tags.
2. **[HIGH]** Add Rust/crate publish strategy to deploy skill (currently web-app biased).
3. **[MEDIUM]** Plan consolidation — detect overlapping plans and merge into single track.

### Three-Axis Growth
| Axis | Score |
|------|-------|
| Technical | 9/10 — 0 → 22 endpoints, 141 tests, streaming, builders, RequestOptions |
| Cognitive | 8/10 — Python SDK local-read workflow, auto-plan worked |
| Process | 6/10 — deploy AskUserQuestion is a 3x-recurring factory defect |

